column1: The early records refer to the site as being Nags Head Lane. The 1890s record sheet says Nags Head Lane = Southbury Road. Nags Head Lane cannot be found but Southbury Road does run into Nags Head Road, east of the site.
The grid reference is taken from the 1950s record sheet and is broadly consistent with the relationship information to the railway station and church described on the sheets

The altitude is taken from the earlier records sheets, which is consistent with the location above. The altitude on the 1940s and 1950s records sheet of 148 ft. is not compatible with the grid reference.
